  "name": "connection-queue",
  "notes": "The accepted not yet connected and recently connected sites are listed within the Connection Queue, including connection point node and ANM status to allow determination of queue position and calculate curtailment. These are the sites that have achieve a Gate 2 outcome following Connections Reform. Please see for detailed Connection Reform outcomes: https://connections.nationalgrid.co.uk/clear-view/\r\n \r\nPlease see the guidance document for further information on how to interpret the Connection Queue.\r\n\r\nTo reference between the bus numbers used in this data set and bus name used within the LTDS please see the [Bus Index](https://connecteddata.nationalgrid.co.uk/dataset/curtailment_buses)",
  "num_resources": 45,
  "num_tags": 7,
  "organization": {
    "id": "a65a370a-a123-4d90-bdb9-fb176c382e83",
    "name": "national_grid_electricity_distribution",
    "title": "National Grid Electricity Distribution",
    "type": "organization",
    "description": "## National Grid Electricity Distribution is the regional electricity distribution division of National Grid.\r\n\r\nFormerly known as Western Power Distribution, the UK\u2019s largest electricity distribution network serves nearly 8 million customers in the East and West Midlands, South West and Wales, delivering essential power to millions of homes and businesses across its regions.\r\n\r\nWith a distribution area of 550,000 square kilometres, it\u2019s 6,500 colleagues are committed to providing a safe, stable and reliable electricity supply and ensuring the highest quality of customer service.",
